However, the vector table seems to be incomplete. It only includes the core system exception handlers and the [`SysTick_Handler`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%7B%22%24mid%22%3A1%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2Fc%3A%2FLearning%2Fembedded%2Fcpp_embedded_stm32_project%2Fhal%2Fstm32f407xx%2Fsrc%2Fstm32f407xx.cpp%22%2C%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%7D%2C%7B%22line%22%3A42%2C%22character%22%3A9%7D%5D "hal/stm32f407xx/src/stm32f407xx.cpp"). For an STM32F407xx microcontroller, the vector table should also include the interrupt handlers for the specific peripherals of the microcontroller.

The interrupt handlers are declared as weak aliases to the `Default_Handler` function, but they are not included in the vector table. You should add them to the [`vectors`](command:_github.copilot.openSymbolFromReferences?%5B%7B%22%24mid%22%3A1%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2Fc%3A%2FLearning%2Fembedded%2Fcpp_embedded_stm32_project%2Fhal%2Fstm32f407xx%2Fstartup.c%22%2C%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%7D%2C%7B%22line%22%3A116%2C%22character%22%3A9%7D%5D "hal/stm32f407xx/startup.c") array in the correct order according to the STM32F407xx microcontroller's reference manual.

