When your code enters a HardFault, it's usually due to an error such as accessing invalid memory, executing an invalid instruction, or a divide-by-zero error. 

To figure out what's causing the HardFault, you can use the ARM Cortex-M Fault Status Registers. These registers provide information about the cause of the fault.

Here's a simple HardFault handler that prints out the values of these registers:

```c
void HardFault_Handler(void)
{
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_pc;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_lr;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_psr;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_r0;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_r1;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_r2;
    volatile uint32_t* stacked_r3;

    asm volatile (
        "MRS r0, MSP\n"
        "B HardFault_Handler_Continue\n"
        "HardFault_Handler_Continue:\n"
        "MOV %[stacked_pc], r0\n"
        : [stacked_pc] "=r" (stacked_pc) :: "r0"
    );

    stacked_pc = (uint32_t*)(*stacked_pc);
    stacked_lr = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 5));
    stacked_psr = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 6));
    stacked_r0 = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 0));
    stacked_r1 = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 1));
    stacked_r2 = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 2));
    stacked_r3 = (uint32_t*)(*(stacked_pc + 3));

    // Print out the values of the registers
    printf("PC = %p\n", stacked_pc);
    printf("LR = %p\n", stacked_lr);
    printf("PSR = %p\n", stacked_psr);
    printf("R0 = %p\n", stacked_r0);
    printf("R1 = %p\n", stacked_r1);
    printf("R2 = %p\n", stacked_r2);
    printf("R3 = %p\n", stacked_r3);

    while(1);
}
```

This code uses inline assembly to get the value of the Main Stack Pointer (MSP), which points to the stack frame that was active when the HardFault occurred. It then uses this to get the values of the Program Counter (PC), Link Register (LR), and xPSR registers, as well as the R0-R3 general purpose registers.

You can then use these values to help debug the cause of the HardFault. For example, the value of the PC register will tell you the instruction that was being executed when the HardFault occurred.

